{"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)PushwooshConfig(cm)getLaunchNotification","symbolKind":"method","title":"getLaunchNotification","fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"+ "},{"text":"getLaunchNotification","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"PushwooshCore"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"getLaunchNotification","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Type Method"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore\/PushwooshConfig\/getLaunchNotification","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"abstract":[{"text":"Returns push notification payload if the app was started in response to a push notification, or ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" otherwise."}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"text","text":"+ ("},{"text":"NSDictionary","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSDictionary"},{"text":" *) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getLaunchNotification","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The push notification payload dictionary, or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" if the app was not launched from a push notification."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this method to retrieve the notification data that caused the app to launch from a terminated state."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is useful for handling deep links or navigation based on the push content."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The value is set when the app is col